parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to hesitate, surge, or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or surges when changing gears
slows down or accelerates randomly
sticks and won't let the driver change gears in manual mode
struggles to change gears in automatic mode
decelerates randomly on the highway
and may shift to reverse gear without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic throttle module can cause the vehicle to surge, hesitate, or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle surges and hesitates when changing gears
slows down or accelerates randomly
and may decelerate randomly on the highway.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the neutral switch (PNP switch) can cause the transmission to shift to reverse gear without warning, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission shifts to reverse gear without warning
the vehicle drops speed rapidly
and the gear indication sign toggles between 'D' and 'R'.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump flange can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to a strong fuel smell inside and outside the vehicle, potentially causing a fire hazard.
symptoms: Strong fuel smell inside and outside the vehicle
fuel splashing around in the tank
fuel leak behind the rear seats.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel System Failure - Fuel Odor and Leaks
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fuel ignition and vapor inhalation, posing a significant risk to the driver and passengers. Prolonged exposure to fuel vapors can also cause health issues.
symptoms: Strong fuel fumes emitting into the interior of the vehicle
fuel odor in the interior and exterior of the vehicle
fuel leaks around the fuel pump and tank
cracked fuel tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ETM can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to potential accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: ETM failure
vehicle malfunction.
